# --- apps/api (Render / Netlify Functions / local) ---
# Local monorepo: you can keep one `.env` at the repo root — `npm run dev:api` loads it.
# Optional override: `apps/api/.env` (loaded first; root fills any missing vars).
# Use the Supabase URI you prefer. If `migrate deploy` fails through the pooler, switch this to
# the "Direct connection" string from Project Settings → Database (host db.*.supabase.co:5432).
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:5432/postgres?schema=public"

# Optional — Prisma 7 + pg adapter: set to false if you hit TLS / certificate errors (e.g. P1010).
# DATABASE_SSL_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=false

# Optional — default 8787 locally; Render sets PORT automatically. Not used on Netlify (serverless).
# PORT=8787
#
# Netlify (Base directory apps/api): set DATABASE_URL, CORS_ORIGIN, etc. in the Netlify UI.
# Install command: cd ../.. && npm ci  ·  Build: prisma migrate deploy (see apps/api/netlify.toml).

# Browser origin(s) allowed to call the API directly (comma-separated). If unset, API uses CORS *.
# CORS_ORIGIN=https://tu-app.vercel.app

# Co-op WebSocket notify (HTTP from API after mutations). Separate WS process: npm run realtime:dev
# COOP_REALTIME_NOTIFY_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3010
# COOP_REALTIME_SECRET=shared-secret

# --- apps/web (Vercel / local Next) ---
# Proxy /api to the API in dev or if you prefer edge rewrites (same-origin fetches).
# API_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8787

# Client-visible WebSocket URL (optional).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_COOP_WS_URL=ws://127.0.0.1:3010/coop-ws
